#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.52"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.52:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.52:0.2"
msgid "6. Sappaññavagga "
msgstr "6. A Wise Person "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 52. Vassaṃvutthasutta → vassavutthaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.52:0.3"
msgid "52. Vassaṃvutthasutta "
msgstr "52. One Who Completed the Rains "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.52:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "sn55.52:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sāvatthiyaṃ vassaṃvuttho kapilavatthuṃ anuppatto hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena. "
msgstr "Now at that time a certain mendicant who had completed the rainy season residence in Sāvatthī arrived at Kapilavatthu on some business. "

msgctxt "sn55.52:1.3"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā: “aññataro kira bhikkhu sāvatthiyaṃ vassaṃvuttho kapilavatthuṃ anuppatto”ti. "
msgstr "The Sakyans of Kapilavatthu heard about this. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.52:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho kāpilavatthavā sakyā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "They went to that mendicant, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "sn55.52:2.2"
msgid "“kacci, bhante, bhagavā arogo ceva balavā cā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, we hope that you’re healthy and well.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.52:2.3"
msgid "“Arogo cāvuso, bhagavā balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“I am, good sirs.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.406, sc3
msgctxt "sn55.52:3.1"
msgid "“Kacci pana, bhante, sāriputtamoggallānā arogā ceva balavanto cā”ti? "
msgstr "“And we hope that Sāriputta and Moggallāna are healthy and well.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.52:3.2"
msgid "“Sāriputtamoggallānāpi kho, āvuso, arogā ceva balavanto cā”ti. "
msgstr "“They are.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn55.52:4.1"
msgid "“Kacci pana, bhante, bhikkhusaṅgho arogo ca balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“And we hope that the mendicant Saṅgha is healthy and well.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.52:4.2"
msgid "“Bhikkhusaṅghopi kho, āvuso, arogo ca balavā cā”ti. "
msgstr "“It is.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn55.52:5.1"
msgid "“Atthi pana te, bhante, kiñci iminā antaravassena bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitan”ti? "
msgstr "“But sir, during this rains residence did you hear and learn anything in the presence of the Buddha?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.52:5.2"
msgid "“Sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "“Good sirs, I heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn55.52:5.3"
msgid "‘appakā te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ye āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharanti. "
msgstr "‘There are fewer mendicants who realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "sn55.52:5.4"
msgid "Atha kho eteva bahutarā bhikkhū ye pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā’ti. "
msgstr "There are more mendicants who, having ended the five lower fetters, are reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn55.52:6.1"
msgid "Aparampi kho me, āvuso, bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "In addition, I heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn55.52:6.2"
msgid "‘appakā te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ye pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "‘There are fewer mendicants who, having ended the five lower fetters, are reborn spontaneously, and will be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

msgctxt "sn55.52:6.3"
msgid "Atha kho eteva bahutarā bhikkhū ye tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissantī’ti. "
msgstr "There are more mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, are once-returners, who come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn55.52:7.1"
msgid "Aparampi kho me, āvuso, bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ: "
msgstr "In addition, I heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn55.52:7.2"
msgid "‘appakā te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ye tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmino, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissanti. "
msgstr "‘There are fewer mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, are once-returners, who come back to this world once only, then make an end of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn55.52:7.3"
msgid "Atha kho eteva bahutarā bhikkhū ye tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā’”ti. "
msgstr "There are more mendicants who, with the ending of three fetters are stream-enterers, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.52:7.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

